    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>\n                  A comparison of SARS-CoV-2 wild-type and the beta variant virus neutralization capacity between 2 and 3 mRNA vaccine series in nursing home residents, and between nursing home and assisted living residents strongly supports 3\n                  <jats:sup>rd</jats:sup>\n                  dose vaccine recommendations, and equivalent polices for nursing homes and assisted living settings. Findings suggest that residents mount a robust humoral response to a 3\n                  <jats:sup>rd</jats:sup>\n                  mRNA vaccination, and have greater neuralization capacity compared to a 2 dose series.\n                </jats:p>",
